<h1>Bad Passwords</h1>

<p>Bad Passwords is a small reference app for delegated password verification. It stores an email address and a URL for that user's Argon2 password hash instead of storing the hash locally.</p>

<p>When someone logs in, the application fetches the current hash from that remote URL, verifies the submitted password against it, and issues a signed JWT if the check succeeds. The home page lets you register a user, exercise the login flow, and inspect the current public key used for token verification.</p>

<%= render "pages/forms", registration_user: @registration_user, login_email: @login_email %>
<%= render "pages/registration_result", registration_result: @registration_result, success_color:, error_color: %>
<%= render "pages/login_result", login_result: @login_result, success_color:, error_color: %>

